snippet.textDisplay: There is not "one" flu virus.  There are MILLIONS of strains.  The flu shot only covers 3 stains but I still recommend getting it every year.  This corona virus is "probably" a very bad strain of the flu. snippet.textDisplay:
Fatality rate depends on the sample constitution and size. If it were serious the fatality rate would remain stable or rise when more people are tested. However, the fatality rate is going down as more are tested, as is the sickness rate. Further, they generally test people who are already sick, so it's further skewed to fool people who don't have any discernment. In addition, there is no control group of people who were proved to be healthy before infection. Research without control groups is too easily open to mistakes and manipulation to be taken seriously by a real scientist.
The PCR test only finds a small amount of RNA, which cannot be proven to be SARS-cov-2, and for anyone who understands the concept of viral load, there need to be millions of actual viruses in your body to indicate any correlation. One virus does not make people sick. The antibody test can only test for antibodies that react to ANY coronavirus, of which there are thousands, so again, there is no indication of infection with this particular virus. Finally, both of these tests are knows to give up to 80% false positive results, depending on the situation, staff expertise and numerous other factors.
While clearly some people are dying of something, shutting down the economy and putting people under house arrest is not only an over-reaction, but a crime against humanity.

So the 2.19 R0 either didn't happen, or more people are immune to this than medical experts & government officials are paying attention to and/or want to admit.

The mortality rate is going to drop as more and more tests become available. I live in the great state of Texas and as of March 6, we had a 6% fatality rate, but as of March 17, it had dropped to 1.68% because more people were getting tested. And while fearmongers want to point out "there are many people who don't know they're infected," they ignore that when it comes to reporting the mortality rate.

There is no vaccine/cure: This hysteria-inducing, fear-mongering tactic blatantly ignores things that naturally happen. There is never a vaccine a cure when something new is introduced. What this report ABSOLUTELY FAILED TO MENTION is that there are vaccines already being worked on by multiple companies AND that there are treatments with 100% SUCCESS RATE already being used by doctors in hospitals.

There will be increases in the number of confirmed cases, not because the disease is rapidly spreading any more, but because tests are becoming available in larger amounts (I know of a US company that is capable of producing 54,000 tests per day [I don't know how many, if any, are being sent to other countries] and that the UK is able to test at least 10,000 per day), but there are also more people recovering from this each day. As of today, there have been 1,041,126 confirmed cases; 221,262 of which have RECOVERED.
